final_output_text: To dry your nails quickly after painting them, we need to consider the principles of heat transfer and evaporation. Both solutions provided involve submerging the nails in water, but they differ in the temperature of the water. 

Solution 0 involves submerging the nails in water at room temperature, while Solution 1 involves submerging the nails in water with ice cubes. 

When you submerge your nails in water, the heat from your body is transferred to the water, causing the water molecules to vibrate and eventually evaporate. This process is known as convection. The faster the water evaporates, the faster your nails will dry. 

In Solution 1, the addition of ice cubes lowers the temperature of the water, which increases the rate of evaporation. This is because colder water molecules have less kinetic energy, allowing them to evaporate more quickly. As a result, the water in Solution 1 will evaporate faster than the water in Solution 0.

Therefore, by submerging your nails in water with ice cubes, you can speed up the evaporation process and dry your nails faster.

The answer is 1.
